Tai-Chi&nbsp; &#39;太極&#39; is a Chinese cosmological term for the &quot;Supreme Ultimate&quot; state of undifferentiated absolute and infinite potentiality.&nbsp;

&nbsp;


TAI-CHI faucet treats hot water as Yang and cold water as Yin, seeming that it blends spirituality in the water and make the process of using water more meaningful. Meanwhile, The gesture of controling the water is similar to Tai-Chi Quan -&nbsp; a kind of traditional Chinese sports.

